August 23 [1938]\x{2014}<<11:15|2>> [Tuesday]
This is Tuesday. Pare came over the week end. Big time. Carol sprained her ankle. Went down to the peninsula with Pare and spent night at Chaplin\x{2019}s place [Ed.\x{2014}Pebble Beach]. Talked all night. Of course, I lost a day of work. I am afraid that Pare doesn\x{2019}t need me on this job and I think he knows it but hasn\x{2019}t admitted it yet. I\x{2019}ll work if I am needed. But I wish I could be left alone until Christmas. I am getting tired\x{2014}very tired. I have at least 6 weeks yet of work by any measuring, and I must re-establish the discipline. Must get tough. So many attractive things are happening that it is difficult. And the ranch on top of everything else. But I must get this done. After all, I\x{2019}ve always worked under some kind of pressure: T.F. while mother was ill, I.D.B while Dad was ill, M & M while this house was going up. Always something. Just more this time. I can do it and I will do it, by God. It is just the discipline that is all. I\x{2019}m wasting time today and I don\x{2019}t care much. Everything goes in circles and I must think WORK. Such strangeness, such strangeness. I\x{2019}ve read parts to people and they like the parts or say they do, but I wonder whether the whole thing will bear up. I wonder. I don\x{2019}t want to get cocky about it. I really shouldn\x{2019}t have told anyone. I get the benefit of the doubt now when before I didn\x{2019}t. The hammering on the next door house is awful. Everything is curious. Pare made me feel better about the country at large. But I am very confused. French rights to I.D.B. are sold now. So many things are happening. This is probably the high point of my life if I only knew it. I will spend today getting straightened out and on a level again\x{2014}thinking. I am fresh again and that is good. My brain is clear for details. I can almost finish in one piece I should think. I want to. I shouldn\x{2019}t be thinking about getting done. Should be thinking only of the story and, by God, I will. I can\x{2019}t let future interfere with the hardest, most complete work of my life. I simply can\x{2019}t. Always I have been weak. Vacillating and miserable. I wish I wouldn\x{2019}t. I wish I weren\x{2019}t. I\x{2019}m so lazy, so damned lazy. This year though I have made up for last year\x{2019}s lay off. I really have batted out a lot of words. I would go through until winter if I could. But if I don\x{2019}t lay off it will be done, and if I do lay off I\x{2019}ll lose the thread. I am simply incapable of working any way but hard and fast. That is the only way I can make it. This is too bad. It is almost impossible in fact but I must get calm and quieted before I can go on. I mean that streak yesterday was curiously indecent. I don\x{2019}t know why but it was. So many things. How impossible it is for me to think. Just writing words, but the thing is starting in my brain. I must get the tempo.",
